  <body><![CDATA[My grandmother would have said "Eleventy-seven" times. However, I would say a dozen or more. During my practice as a prosecuting attorney, I regularly returned to the book to remind me it was my job to do the right thing. I discovered the book around the seventh grade. It became one of my "summer" books, to which I turned in celebration of school being out for the summer. My first reads were childish. As an adult I have found more significant reasons to return to this novel time and again.]]></body>
  
