  <body><![CDATA[Howard, as much as I love To Kill A Mockingbird (and Flannery O'Connor), I suspect Flannery O'Connor would have been inclined to disagree with your addendum. Her literary worldview was, I think, tempered by her daily struggle and the trials in her life. Her work and her reality left little room for sentimentality. I don't think her craft and vision was ever very comfortable with the things that tugged at heartstrings. My take on that comment regarding Mockingbird was that she truly believed it belonged in the children's hour.]]></body>
  
