  <body><![CDATA[<i>Jan wrote: "I just read your Mockingbird review for the first time, Mike. It's such a hopeful thing! Thanks!"</i><br /><br />Jan, my thanks for your reading and commenting. Yes, I wanted to make this as hopeful as possible. And I think it was Harper Lee's intent to write about hope, even in the face of adversity and injustice. <br /><br />I have become jaded by our national leaders. I find it is all too often the conscience of an unsung individual whose actions spread further and with more consequence to meet the needs in the community either unseen or ignored by our Congress and Senate.<br /><br />That is why I hold out hope for all the Scouts and Jems to discover the hope presented by Harper Lee so that we might live in a more caring nation led by those who follow in our footsteps.]]></body>
  
