  <body><![CDATA[<i>Matt wrote: "Oh, I'm sorry! I was so excited to write that I think I was unclear. I agree completely that MLK was a revolutionary. The picture that we present of him in schools and civic discourse, however, is ..."</i><br /><br />Not long ago I saw Cornel West, in essence, make this very point when he cited the fact that MLK only had a forty percent approval rating within the black community at the time of his death. Time and canonization has a way of blurring the realities of the times. This is also true of artistic works, including literature. So many that are now revered were controversial or not popular in their day, because they were ahead of the curve and challenged the status quo.]]></body>
  
